  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes </strong>(skins on) into wedges</p><p>Add the <strong>wedges</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until the wedges are tender and starting to crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/southern-fried-halloumi-with-wedges-and-slaw/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut your <strong>halloumi</strong> into 2 equal sized slices per person</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/southern-fried-halloumi-with-wedges-and-slaw/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a handful of<strong> flour</strong> to a plate</p><p>Crack your <strong>egg[s]</strong> into a shallow bowl and beat with a fork</p><p>Add your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> to a plate with your <strong>dried oregano</strong>, <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> and a very generous pinch of <strong>black pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up – these are your <strong>seasoned panko breadcrumbs</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/southern-fried-halloumi-with-wedges-and-slaw/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Coat the <strong>halloumi slices</strong> in the<strong> flour</strong>, tap off the excess, then dip them into the <strong>beaten egg</strong> and press them into the <strong>seasoned panko breadcrumbs </strong>firmly to coat everything evenly</p><p>Tip: Make sure the halloumi slices are fully coated in the breadcrumbs on all sides!</p><p>Put in the fridge until later to firm up – these are your <strong>breaded halloumi slices</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/southern-fried-halloumi-with-wedges-and-slaw/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top, tail, peel and grate your<strong> carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>grated carrot</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>shredded red cabbage</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/southern-fried-halloumi-with-wedges-and-slaw/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>cider vinegar</strong> and <strong>mayo</strong> to the bowl with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and stir it all together – this is your<strong> slaw</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>red</strong> <strong>chilli relish </strong>with 10ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[15ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[20ml] </span>water<strong> </strong>– this is your <strong>chilli dip</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/southern-fried-halloumi-with-wedges-and-slaw/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once the pan is hot, add the <strong>breaded</strong> <strong>halloumi slices</strong> and cook for 4-5 min on each side or until golden and crispy</p><p>Transfer onto kitchen paper to soak up any excess oil – this is your<strong> Southern fried halloumi</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/southern-fried-halloumi-with-wedges-and-slaw/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Southern fried halloumi</strong> with the<strong> wedges</strong>, <strong>slaw </strong>and<strong> chilli dip </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
